This paper focuses on the use of relational database access technologies in software projects, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The use of object-relational mapping technologies also involves programming language (cs.PL) concepts and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the analysis of the probability of introducing technologies over time and the co-occurrence of multiple technologies within the same project falls under the systems and information theory (cs.SI) sub-category.
